What does cobalt-59 do? Cobalt-59 is a radioactive isotope of cobalt that has a half-life of 5.27 years. It is used in the medical industry to treat cancer and to diagnose and treat other medical conditions.
What particles are used to bombard cobalt-59 to make cobalt-60? Cobalt-59 is bombarded with neutrons to produce cobalt-60.

Why do countries protect their firms in international trade? Governments protect their firms in international trade for a few reasons. The most common reason is that the government wants to create and protect jobs in the country. Additionally, the government may want to ensure that the country has a strong industrial base so it can produce goods and services that it can sell to other countries. Finally, the government may want to ensure that its citizens have access to high-quality, affordable goods and services.
Additional dietary protein may cause what? A diet high in protein may cause constipation.
What will too much protein do to you? Too much protein can overload your kidneys and liver, and can also lead to dehydration.

what is part of redistribution-with-growth policy approach? Redistribution-with-growth policy approach is a policy approach that focuses on reducing income inequality while promoting economic growth. This approach typically includes a variety of policies aimed at redistributing wealth and income, such as progressive taxation and government spending on social programs.

what is part of redistribution-with-growth policy approach? is land reform part of that? Redistribution with growth is a policy approach that strives to reduce inequality while promoting economic growth. Land reform is one component of this approach, though it is not universally agreed upon as to its effectiveness.

what is part of redistribution-with-growth policy approach? is land reform part of that? Is increased access to education part of that? Some elements of a redistribution-with-growth policy approach include land reform, increased access to education, and increased access to health care.
